sp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><b><span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;line-heig=
ht:105%;font-family:&quot;Book Antiqua&quot;,serif">New Goal to Enroll 2 mi=
llion More Borrowers in Plans like Pay As You Earn (PAYE).</span></b><span =
style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:105%;font-family:&quot;Book Antiqua&q=
uot;,serif">
 The President&#8217;s PAYE and related income-driven repayment plans are a=
vailable to help borrowers who may be struggling to manage their debt effec=
tively.&nbsp;Yet, too many borrowers still do not know about this important=
 option.&nbsp;Leveraging key improvements in loan
 servicing and customer service, better tools and resources, targeted outre=
ach to borrowers, and partnerships with key external organizations under th=
e Student Debt Challenge, the Administration is announcing a new goal to en=
roll two million more borrowers
 in plans like PAYE by this time next year. <b><o:p></o:p></b></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><b><span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;=
