 experts to apply to securely access and match administrative student aid d=
ata files with other survey and administrative data, while ensuring safegua=
rds are in place to protect the privacy of students and families. AID build=
s on the Administration&#8217;s recent
 efforts to leverage government data in ways that can improve service deliv=
ery, promote transparency, and strengthen accountability, particularly thro=
ugh the College Scorecard, which includes the most comprehensive, reliable =
data ever published on students&#8217;
 post-college earnings and repayment outcomes. The Department is also explo=
ring future opportunities for new research partnerships.<b><o:p></o:p></b><=
/span></p>
