 released last October,&nbsp;in consultation with the Department of the Tre=
asury and CFPB, the report outlined a series of statutory, regulatory and a=
dministrative recommendations to safeguard student borrowers including call=
ing on Congress to simplify income-driven
 repayment plans; ensuring service members don&#8217;t lose their interest =
rate protections under the Servicemember Civil Relief Act when consolidatin=
g their loans; strengthening protections against predatory third parties th=
at charge borrowers exorbitant fees for
 services that are available for free at studentaid.gov and enhancing feder=
al data-sharing to improve borrower experiences and simplify the applicatio=
n process for borrowers<span style=3D"color:#1F497D">&#8217;</span> to re-c=
ertify eligibility for income-driven repayment
 over multiple years. <o:p></o:p></span></li></ul>
